If an institution is referred to a State for review under the SPRP, the institution must satisfy the State's standards.
If the institution was not otherwise required to keep records relating to its compliance with State Standards, and
it did not keep those records, the Secretary agrees that the State should allow an institution a reasonable period
of time to obtain records and information to enable the institution to demonstrate its compliance with the State's
standards.


