 None. 



Comments:

 Several comments were received recommending that an institution's financial aid officer be included in the list
of personnel that are required to have precertification training. 



Discussion:

 Pursuant to the administrative capability standards set out in  668.16, every institution is required to designate
a capable individual that is responsible for administering the Title IV, HEA programs at the institution. This designated
individual, who is usually a financial aid administrator, is required to have precertification training. 



