Discussion: 

The Secretary believes that the borrower is entitled to a loan discharge under the HEA in any case in which a student's
program of education is disrupted by the closing of the school to the extent that the student does not, for any reason,
complete the program. The presumption must be that the school's closing directly hindered the student's achievement
